Russia: Death of Child in Vladimir Region
-----------------------------------------
An 8-year-old girl died of rabies in the city of Goose-Khrustalniy in the
Vladimir region. [Over a 2-month period] 200 people have received medical
treatment in hospitals in the city of Goose-Khrustalniy due to animal
bites. A rabies quarantine has been declared in 4 areas of the city, and 30
more areas are [at risk]. A similar situation pertains in other towns of
the Vladimir region (Murom, Alexandrov, Petushki, Kirzhach and Yuriev-Polskiy).
--
Natalia Pshenichnaya
<crane@aaanet.ru>
[The Vladimir region is located in the center of the European part of
Russia (in the central part of the East European plain). It borders the
regions of Ryazan, Moscow, Yaroslavl, Nizhniy Novgorod, and Ivanovo. The
total area of the region is 29 thousand sq. km, and the population is 1 574
000. The population of the city of Goose-Khrystalniy is 67 000. - Corresp.NP]
